FBIS3-9771 "dreeu061__a94011" FBIS-EEU-94-061-A Document Type:Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 ANNEX Bulgaria Spokesman Comments on Daskalov's Albania Visit AU3003134594 Sofia BTA in English 1253 GMT 30 Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU3003134594 Sofia BTA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Sofia, March 30 (BTA) -- In the course of his formal visit to Albania completed yesterday, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov and his Albanian partners expressed a wish to promote bilateral relations to build up trust in the Balkans. Foreign Ministry spokesman Radko Vlaykov today met the press to elaborate on the visit. Asked if Bulgaria and Albania differed on the UN Security Council decision to send Turkish peacekeepers to former Yugoslavia, Vlaykov said this issue was only considered in the course of the general review of the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina. Daskalov reiterated the Bulgarian call on neighbouring countries to refrain from participation in the UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces]. Vlaykov said during a joint press conference of the Bulgarian and Albanian foreign ministers in Tirana yesterday, Daskalov was asked about the Bulgarian position on Kosovo. He said Bulgaria opposed any interference by foreign forces in seeking a solution to this internal problem.
